AN ACT relating to offenders; [requiring] prohibiting the Director of the
Department of Corrections from taking certain actions relating to
[discharge] certain debts upon the release of an offender from prison;
and providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the Director of the Department of Corrections to take certain actions
2 upon the release of an offender from prison. (NRS 209.511) Section 1 of this bill [requires]
3 prohibits the Director from collecting or attempting to [discharge] collect any outstanding
4 medical debt owed by an offender to the Department upon the release of the offender from
5 prison. Section 1 also: (1) prohibits the Director from reporting information relating to
6 any such debt to a consumer reporting agency; and (2) authorizes the Director to
7 continue collection efforts if the offender is returned to the custody of the Department.
8 Section 1.5 of this bill [requires] applies the [Director of the Department] amendatory
9 provisions of section 1 to [discharge any outstanding medical debt owed to the Department
10 by] an offender who has been released from prison by the expiration of his or her term of
11 sentence or by pardon or parole before July 1, 2025. Section 1.3 of this bill makes a
12 conforming change to refer to provisions that have been renumbered by section 1.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
